17
00:00:12,255 --> 00:00:12,372
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,373 --> 00:00:15,373
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,397 --> 00:00:20,274
<i>War in the Expansion Region!</i>

20
00:00:20,358 --> 00:00:24,403
<i>As the Separatists tighten their grip
over vital but isolated supply routes,</i>

21
00:00:24,529 --> 00:00:26,614
<i>the Republic launches a lightning strike</i>

22
00:00:26,656 --> 00:00:30,868
<i>into a remote, ghost nebula,
to control the strategic system of Um bar a.</i>

23
00:00:30,952 --> 00:00:34,121
<i>Republic forces smash
through the Separatist blockade</i>

24
00:00:34,163 --> 00:00:37,124
<i>in an effort to claim the shadowy world.</i>

25
00:00:44,674 --> 00:00:47,468
Masters Krell and Tiin will be
supporting my troops in the south,

26
00:00:47,552 --> 00:00:49,845
while Anakin's battalion comes in
from the north

27
00:00:49,929 --> 00:00:51,931
and takes out enemy reinforcements.

28
00:00:51,973 --> 00:00:54,100
It is imperative
that we conquer the capital city

29
00:00:54,141 --> 00:00:55,476
as quickly as possible,

30
00:00:55,935 --> 00:00:57,144
and hold it.

31
00:00:57,228 --> 00:00:59,522
Our biggest problem
is gonna be the local militia.

32
00:00:59,605 --> 00:01:01,983
The Umbarans have aligned themselves
with the Separatists

33
00:01:02,066 --> 00:01:03,150
and are heavily armed.

34
00:01:03,317 --> 00:01:06,529
ARC Trooper Fives will be
assisting my units on special assignment.

35
00:01:06,696 --> 00:01:08,739
Ready to do my part, General Skywalker.

36
00:01:09,156 --> 00:01:12,535
-Nice to have you on board.
-Just like old times, Rex.

37
00:01:12,618 --> 00:01:16,205
Remember, Anakin, Cody and I will be
12 clicks to your south.

38
00:01:16,289 --> 00:01:18,624
We're counting on you
to take out those local fighters,

39
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:21,836
or, I'm afraid,
the capital will never surrender.

40
00:01:22,336 --> 00:01:25,381
Does my battalion
have to do everything?

41
00:01:25,881 --> 00:01:28,092
You seem to always volunteer.

42
00:01:31,345 --> 00:01:33,097
All right, let's go!

43
00:02:12,637 --> 00:02:14,722
There's a lot of surface fire.

44
00:02:14,805 --> 00:02:17,433
They ain't got nothing we can't handle, sir.

45
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:24,607
-You hanging in there, Tup?
-So far so good, Captain.

46
00:02:25,566 --> 00:02:27,735
<i>General Skywalker,
I've turned the lights out.</i>

47
00:02:28,069 --> 00:02:30,905
Our night vision sensors
are having a tough time in this chop.

48
00:02:30,946 --> 00:02:32,865
I hope we don't overshoot the landing site.

49
00:02:33,157 --> 00:02:35,242
Just get us as close as you can.

50
00:02:38,079 --> 00:02:40,164
Time to lock and load!

51
00:03:12,446 --> 00:03:14,281
-After them, boys!
-All right!

52
00:03:14,323 --> 00:03:16,242
-Let's go!
-Let's do it!

53
00:04:00,369 --> 00:04:02,079
Go, go! Go, go, go!

54
00:04:02,163 --> 00:04:03,330
Give it to them!

55
00:04:04,331 --> 00:04:06,500
Go, go, go!

56
00:04:07,001 --> 00:04:09,295
Take them out! Take them all out!

57
00:04:10,504 --> 00:04:12,131
That's the stuff!

58
00:04:13,674 --> 00:04:14,967
Incoming!

59
00:04:26,729 --> 00:04:28,063
That's it.

60
00:04:28,522 --> 00:04:30,191
Give it to them!

61
00:04:32,109 --> 00:04:33,736
Let's go, let's go!

62
00:04:33,819 --> 00:04:35,196
Go, go! Go, go, go!

63
00:04:41,118 --> 00:04:43,746
The planet has a ridge
at 23 degrees, north-northwest.

64
00:04:43,829 --> 00:04:46,665
Good. We can use it as a staging area.

65
00:04:46,707 --> 00:04:48,375
That's it!
Take them around the right.

66
00:04:49,335 --> 00:04:53,756
Keep moving. We've gotta claim that ridge.
The other battalions are counting on us.

67
00:04:54,173 --> 00:04:55,424
Let's go!

68
00:05:06,769 --> 00:05:08,229
Don't stray too far.

69
00:05:08,270 --> 00:05:11,482
The enemy could have
the whole place rigged with traps.

70
00:05:11,565 --> 00:05:13,150
I can't even see the enemy!

71
00:05:16,403 --> 00:05:19,365
That's why they're called
the Shadow People, Tup.

72
00:05:21,575 --> 00:05:22,660
Everybody, take cover!

73
00:05:23,285 --> 00:05:24,662
Go, go, go!

74
00:05:27,373 --> 00:05:30,209
Look, it's just a vine.
Keep moving, Hard case.

75
00:05:30,251 --> 00:05:32,670
Yeah, I got it all under control.

76
00:05:54,066 --> 00:05:55,734
That's not right!

77
00:06:08,414 --> 00:06:09,957
Nice work, Fives.

78
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:13,544
-Hard case, right?
-Yeah, that's what they call me.

79
00:06:49,580 --> 00:06:51,373
General Kenobi's battalion, sir?

80
00:06:51,498 --> 00:06:53,167
They're pushing towards the capital.

81
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:56,128
We'll need to move out
as soon as the men are ready.

82
00:06:56,170 --> 00:06:58,172
All platoons have reported in, General.

83
00:06:58,672 --> 00:07:01,008
-Get some rest.
-Thank you, sir.

84
00:07:01,467 --> 00:07:02,468
I'm fine.

85
00:07:02,801 --> 00:07:05,095
The General's giving you an order, Dogma.

86
00:07:05,179 --> 00:07:06,680
Of course, sir!

87
00:07:07,848 --> 00:07:10,225
He's wound tight, but he's loyal.

88
00:07:11,268 --> 00:07:13,479
He kind of reminds me of you.

89
00:07:13,604 --> 00:07:16,065
Maybe, back in the day.

90
00:07:45,219 --> 00:07:46,929
-What is that?
-Look out!

91
00:07:56,397 --> 00:07:58,565
Ambush ! They're behind us!

92
00:08:07,658 --> 00:08:09,410
The enemy's circled behind us.

93
00:08:09,493 --> 00:08:11,078
Everybody, we must defend our backs!

94
00:08:20,713 --> 00:08:22,840
Call in an air strike on the enemy positions.

95
00:08:22,923 --> 00:08:25,092
Let's hope they're not too busy
helping Obi-Wan.

96
00:08:25,426 --> 00:08:27,094
There's an opening to our south.

97
00:08:27,177 --> 00:08:29,179
I recommend we move
all platoons off the ridge

98
00:08:29,263 --> 00:08:31,098
in case the air strike overshoots.

99
00:08:31,724 --> 00:08:32,933
Good thinking, Rex.

100
00:08:32,975 --> 00:08:35,728
Everyone, move out, now!

101
00:09:05,299 --> 00:09:06,300
All here, sir.

102
00:09:06,383 --> 00:09:08,886
Stay covered. We have to hold the position.

103
00:09:10,971 --> 00:09:13,640
Are you sure those bombers are coming?

104
00:09:23,025 --> 00:09:24,443
Good old Odd Ball.

105
00:09:24,485 --> 00:09:25,527
Always on target.

106
00:09:30,908 --> 00:09:33,327
-Glad we got off that ridge.
-Yeah.

107
00:09:33,660 --> 00:09:36,038
That'll teach them.

108
00:09:57,101 --> 00:09:58,393
General Krell's here?

109
00:09:58,477 --> 00:10:00,312
Something big must be going on.

110
00:10:01,980 --> 00:10:05,109
Master Krell, my thanks for the air support.

111
00:10:05,192 --> 00:10:06,819
Indeed, General Skywalker.

112
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:10,447
The locals have proven to be
more resourceful than we anticipated.

113
00:10:10,697 --> 00:10:12,866
But that's not the reason for your visit?

114
00:10:13,117 --> 00:10:14,118
No.

115
00:10:14,201 --> 00:10:17,955
The Council has ordered you
back to Coruscant, effective immediately.

116
00:10:18,288 --> 00:10:20,374
What? Why?

117
00:10:20,707 --> 00:10:23,836
I'm afraid a request was made
by the Supreme Chancellor,

118
00:10:23,877 --> 00:10:25,420
and the Council obliged.

119
00:10:25,504 --> 00:10:26,630
That is all they would tell me.

120
00:10:27,131 --> 00:10:29,133
Well, I can't just leave my men.

121
00:10:29,299 --> 00:10:31,635
I'll be taking over in the interim.

122
00:10:31,718 --> 00:10:33,971
Don't worry about a thing, sir.

123
00:10:34,054 --> 00:10:37,224
We'll have this city under Republic control
by the time you're back.

124
00:10:37,266 --> 00:10:41,395
Master Krell, this is Rex,
my first in command.

125
00:10:41,478 --> 00:10:44,231
You won't find a finer
and more loyal trooper anywhere.

126
00:10:44,773 --> 00:10:45,899
Good to hear that.

127
00:10:45,983 --> 00:10:48,152
I wish you well, Skywalker.

128
00:11:05,419 --> 00:11:09,423
Your reputation precedes you, General.
It is an honor to be serving you.

129
00:11:09,464 --> 00:11:12,092
I find it very interesting, Captain,

130
00:11:12,134 --> 00:11:14,720
that you are able to recognize
the value of honor,

131
00:11:14,761 --> 00:11:16,054
for a clone.

132
00:11:17,556 --> 00:11:19,266
Stand at attention when I address you.

133
00:11:21,268 --> 00:11:25,063
Your flattery is duly noted,
but it will not be rewarded.

134
00:11:25,105 --> 00:11:27,065
There's a reason
my command is so effective,

135
00:11:27,482 --> 00:11:31,862
and it's because I do things by the book,
and that includes protocol.

136
00:11:32,446 --> 00:11:34,990
Have all platoons ready
to move out immediately.

137
00:11:35,199 --> 00:11:36,241
That is all.

138
00:11:48,212 --> 00:11:49,546
Quicken that pace, battalion.

139
00:11:49,755 --> 00:11:52,299
This isn't some training course on Kamino.

140
00:11:52,341 --> 00:11:55,469
The new general has a way with words.

141
00:11:55,552 --> 00:11:57,512
He's just trying to keep us on schedule.

142
00:11:57,596 --> 00:11:59,264
By raising everyone's ire?

143
00:11:59,431 --> 00:12:02,559
Either way, he's in charge,
and we've got a job to do.

144
00:12:02,643 --> 00:12:05,062
Just treat him with respect,
and we'll all get along fine.

145
00:12:05,812 --> 00:12:06,897
Do you see that?

146
00:12:08,941 --> 00:12:10,484
Yeah. Ready your weapons.

147
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:49,398
Anyone else wanna
stop and play with the animals?

148
00:12:51,733 --> 00:12:53,026
Didn't think so.

149
00:12:53,610 --> 00:12:55,237
Now keep moving!

150
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:12,087
Sir, we've been keeping this pace
for 12 hours now.

151
00:13:12,170 --> 00:13:13,964
The men are getting worn down.

152
00:13:14,047 --> 00:13:15,799
We should rest.

153
00:13:18,343 --> 00:13:20,929
General Krell, the top of this ridge
will make a good place

154
00:13:21,013 --> 00:13:22,264
for the men to make camp.

155
00:13:22,347 --> 00:13:24,016
The men don't need rest.

156
00:13:24,057 --> 00:13:27,060
They need the resolve
to complete the task at hand.

157
00:13:27,144 --> 00:13:31,481
-But, sir...
-CT-7567, are you reading me?

158
00:13:31,732 --> 00:13:33,567
Excuse me, sir?

159
00:13:33,734 --> 00:13:37,446
I asked you a question, CT-7567.

160
00:13:37,529 --> 00:13:40,657
Do you understand the need
to adhere to my strategy?

161
00:13:40,741 --> 00:13:43,910
Sir, the terrain is extremely hostile.

162
00:13:43,994 --> 00:13:48,165
Despite the difficulty of the conditions,
the battalion is making good time.

163
00:13:48,248 --> 00:13:51,126
-These men just need a little break.
-Captain,

164
00:13:51,209 --> 00:13:52,252
do I need to remind you

165
00:13:52,336 --> 00:13:56,048
of this battalion's strategic mission
in conquering this planet?

166
00:13:56,089 --> 00:13:57,090
Look back.

167
00:13:57,424 --> 00:13:58,592
See those platoons?

168
00:13:59,051 --> 00:14:01,970
Their mission is to take this city
and take it swiftly.

169
00:14:02,054 --> 00:14:05,599
Time and rest are luxuries
the Republic cannot afford.

170
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:07,934
We are the key to this invasion.

171
00:14:08,143 --> 00:14:10,645
The other battalions
are counting on our support.

172
00:14:10,729 --> 00:14:14,941
If we fail, everyone fails!
Do you understand this?

173
00:14:15,359 --> 00:14:17,611
Do all of you understand this?

174
00:14:18,153 --> 00:14:19,654
Now, move on!

175
00:14:34,378 --> 00:14:36,755
Sir, we're ready
to bring our forward platoons in

176
00:14:36,797 --> 00:14:38,757
for a surgical strike on the city's defenses.

177
00:14:38,924 --> 00:14:41,843
-There won't be any need, Captain.
-Sir?

178
00:14:41,927 --> 00:14:45,847
All platoons will execute a forward assault
along the main route to the city.

179
00:14:45,972 --> 00:14:50,977
But, sir, General Skywalker's plan was
to surprise them with multiple attacks.

180
00:14:51,061 --> 00:14:52,646
If we come in from the main route,

181
00:14:52,687 --> 00:14:55,273
they're likely to engage us
in a full frontal assault.

182
00:14:55,315 --> 00:14:58,902
Change of plans, Captain.
I'm in command now.

183
00:14:59,152 --> 00:15:03,156
With all due respect, General,
we don't know what we are up against.

184
00:15:03,198 --> 00:15:05,158
It might be wiser to think first.

185
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,202
Are you questioning my order?

186
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:11,832
This battalion will take the main road
straight to the capital.

187
00:15:11,915 --> 00:15:12,916
You will not stop,

188
00:15:12,999 --> 00:15:16,002
and you will not turn back,
regardless of the resistance you meet.

189
00:15:16,837 --> 00:15:21,842
We will attack them with all our troops,
not some sneak attack with a few men.

190
00:15:21,925 --> 00:15:25,679
That is my order.
And you will follow it explicitly.

191
00:15:25,804 --> 00:15:29,850
Do I make myself clear, CT-7567?

192
00:15:30,517 --> 00:15:31,935
Yes, General.

193
00:15:32,018 --> 00:15:33,937
Now, engage!

194
00:15:53,373 --> 00:15:55,709
So, why aren't we sticking
to the original plan,

195
00:15:55,792 --> 00:15:58,044
and probing the city defenses first?

196
00:15:58,128 --> 00:16:00,714
We can do this. Let's take them.

197
00:16:00,755 --> 00:16:03,550
Yeah, leave it to Hard case
to dive in head first.

198
00:16:03,925 --> 00:16:05,886
The General's new plan is reckless.

199
00:16:05,969 --> 00:16:09,764
You ever think that maybe
the General knows what he is doing?

200
00:16:09,848 --> 00:16:12,976
I know you think this is a bad idea.

201
00:16:13,059 --> 00:16:15,979
I raised my objection
to General Krell's plan,

202
00:16:16,062 --> 00:16:17,481
but he didn't agree.

203
00:16:17,564 --> 00:16:19,191
So, this is it.

204
00:16:19,566 --> 00:16:21,568
What if he's wrong? Then what?

205
00:16:21,985 --> 00:16:26,114
This isn't the time for a debate.
Right now, we have to stay alert.

206
00:16:33,288 --> 00:16:36,750
Eh, it's too quiet out there.

207
00:16:48,762 --> 00:16:50,180
Mines! Nobody move!

208
00:17:02,192 --> 00:17:03,193
Oz is down.

209
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:05,487
So is Ringo.

210
00:17:06,571 --> 00:17:08,281
Can you sweep them?

211
00:17:10,534 --> 00:17:12,160
There are more over here.

212
00:17:12,244 --> 00:17:14,788
Looks like the whole road's
been booby trapped.

213
00:17:15,455 --> 00:17:17,582
Everyone, watch your step.

214
00:17:27,968 --> 00:17:29,469
We're completely exposed.

215
00:17:29,928 --> 00:17:30,929
Hold your ground!

216
00:17:32,472 --> 00:17:34,140
You want a piece of this?

217
00:17:39,020 --> 00:17:41,439
Uh-oh. I think Hard case made them mad.

218
00:17:46,945 --> 00:17:47,946
We're blown!

219
00:17:48,405 --> 00:17:50,073
The Umbarans are advancing.

220
00:17:51,324 --> 00:17:52,951
Make them eat heat.

221
00:18:15,682 --> 00:18:16,850
They're coming from all directions!

222
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,435
We don't have any cover!

223
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,978
We need to pull back.

224
00:18:20,020 --> 00:18:23,189
Get them to follow us.
If we can draw them out, we can see them.

225
00:18:23,273 --> 00:18:25,859
If we can see them, we can hit them.

226
00:18:26,276 --> 00:18:29,195
All squads, pull back now!

227
00:18:30,113 --> 00:18:31,823
This can't be good.

228
00:18:45,045 --> 00:18:46,546
Feeble minded clones!

229
00:18:48,006 --> 00:18:50,425
Get in there and save their necks.

230
00:18:54,554 --> 00:18:56,681
Get ready. Here they come!

231
00:19:07,859 --> 00:19:10,779
Stand back.
Hit them with everything you got.

232
00:19:17,077 --> 00:19:18,078
Where are you going?

233
00:19:18,328 --> 00:19:19,871
Get back here!

234
00:19:24,417 --> 00:19:25,794
They're pulling back.

235
00:19:29,089 --> 00:19:31,049
CT-7567.

236
00:19:31,591 --> 00:19:34,260
Do you have a malfunction in your design?

237
00:19:34,344 --> 00:19:36,930
You've pulled your forces back
from taking the capital city.

238
00:19:37,430 --> 00:19:39,516
The enemy now has control of this route.

239
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:42,352
This entire operation
has been compromised,

240
00:19:42,435 --> 00:19:44,104
because of your failure.

241
00:19:44,312 --> 00:19:49,234
General Krell, in case you haven't noticed,
Captain Rex just saved this platoon.

242
00:19:49,275 --> 00:19:52,070
Surely you won't fail to recognize that.

243
00:19:52,445 --> 00:19:54,322
ARC-5555,

244
00:19:54,948 --> 00:19:56,574
stand down.

245
00:19:57,409 --> 00:19:59,786
Sir. Yes, sir.

246
00:19:59,869 --> 00:20:05,208
Sir, if I may address your accusation,
I followed your orders.

247
00:20:05,291 --> 00:20:09,546
Even in the face of a plan,
that was, in my opinion, severely flawed.

248
00:20:09,796 --> 00:20:11,214
A plan that cost us men.

249
00:20:11,297 --> 00:20:13,174
Not clones! Men!

250
00:20:15,301 --> 00:20:19,180
As sure as it is my duty
to remain loyal to your command,

251
00:20:19,764 --> 00:20:23,309
I also have another duty.
To protect those men.

252
00:20:25,979 --> 00:20:30,483
You have a spark of tenacity, Captain.
I'll give you that.

253
00:20:30,567 --> 00:20:34,320
I know that I don't command
like the Jedi you're used to serving,

254
00:20:34,362 --> 00:20:38,074
certainly not like General Skywalker,
but I have my way.

255
00:20:38,908 --> 00:20:42,662
It may be difficult,
but these are difficult times.

256
00:20:42,746 --> 00:20:45,039
And it's proven effective.

257
00:20:45,123 --> 00:20:48,501
And I suppose your loyalty to your men
is to be commended.

258
00:20:48,585 --> 00:20:50,879
They seem to admire this.

259
00:20:50,962 --> 00:20:53,339
That's important
to an effective commander.

260
00:20:54,549 --> 00:20:58,887
All right, Captain Rex,
your opinion has been noted.

261
00:20:59,637 --> 00:21:01,264
Dismissed.

262
00:21:04,184 --> 00:21:06,394
I think he almost complimented you.

263
00:21:07,604 --> 00:21:08,605
It's hard to tell.

264
00:21:08,813 --> 00:21:09,939
Incoming!

265
00:21:15,403 --> 00:21:16,863
Get back! Get back!

266
00:21:17,238 --> 00:21:19,449
The Umbarans must have regrouped
for a counterattack.

267
00:21:19,532 --> 00:21:21,951
Everyone, we must hold this position!

268
00:21:22,368 --> 00:21:24,412
You think General Krell
still intends on taking the capital

269
00:21:24,496 --> 00:21:25,914
using this strategy?

270
00:21:25,997 --> 00:21:29,417
I don't know. I'll get back to you on that
if we survive this battle.

271
00:21:29,441 --> 00:21:31,441
http://hiqve.com/

